in basketball, the full 2014 induction class of the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame is announced. Players Alonzo Mourning and Mitch Richmond, coaches Nolan Richardson and Gary Williams, and the Immaculata College women's team of 1972–1974 will join five individuals announced in February (players Šarūnas Marčiulionis and Guy Rodgers, coach Bob "Slick" Leonard, and contributors Nathaniel Clifton and David Stern). (AP via ESPN)